# Expo Go first, stay small

## Default dev flow

- **`npm start`** (Expo Go + QR) is the only required dev path. Do not make Xcode, `expo run:ios`, or a custom dev client necessary for normal work.
- `start`, `dev`, and `go` must all run `scripts/start-go.js` — never `--dev-client` by default.
- Optional native paths (`dev:client`, `ios`, `ios:sim`) stay secondary; document them in DEPLOY-DEV-CLIENT.md only.

## Adding features

Before adding a dependency or native module, check it runs in **Expo Go SDK 54**:

- Prefer packages bundled with Expo (`expo-*`, SDK-aligned `react-native-*`).
- Avoid `expo prebuild`, custom native code, or plugins that require a dev client unless there is no Expo Go alternative.
- If a feature needs a native module Expo Go lacks, say so explicitly and keep Expo Go working for everything else.

## Keep it small and simple

- Minimize scope: smallest correct diff; no extra abstractions or helpers.
- Minimize bundle size: one compressed overview map; camera zoom reuses it — no extra map tiers.
- Minimize dependencies: do not add packages when existing Expo/RN APIs suffice.
- Prefer one clear implementation (e.g. SVG camera transform + hit targets) over parallel GPU/coordinate paths.
- Do not add tests, docs, or scripts unless they support the change or are requested.

## Map (Expo Go compatible)

- Fixed SVG `viewBox`, **one merged overview path** — static by default for performance.
- **Detail-strip zoom only** — animated camera (`AnimatedG` + `matrix`); no pinch/pan.
- Taps: transparent SVG hit targets (`Rect` + `onPress`).
- Prefecture: dot on overview; readable label overlay when zoomed.

## Scripts checklist when touching dev tooling

- [ ] `npm run check:expo-go` passes
- [ ] `npm start` launches Expo Go (no `--dev-client`)
- [ ] README and DEPLOY-IPHONE.md still describe QR → Expo Go as primary
- [ ] New production deps added to `scripts/expo-go-policy.json` allowlist only if Expo Go–compatible
